results.name: Assign weights to the nonnegative integers as in A073327, then sort them by weight.
comment: We are using U.S. spelling, as in A108067 rather than A004740, and we ignore hyphens and spaces.
In the case of ties, sort by numerical value.
example: Let wt(n) = A073327(n) denote the weight of n. We have wt(1) = 34 < wt(10) = 39 < wt(5) = 42 = wt(9) = 42 < wt(8) = 49 < ...
results.author: _Matthew Goers_, Oct 26 2009, Nov 02 2009, Nov 03 2009
